===Etymology===
{{ja-kanjitab|たこ|yomi=k|alt=章魚,鮹,鱆}}
{{swp|ja:}}
[[file:Octopus vulgaris2.jpg|thumb|right|200px|蛸(tako)]]

{{rfe|ja}}

There are multiple theories regarding the origin of this word, but they tend to agree in interpreting the initial ''ta-'' as the {{ja-hfk|手|て|[[hand]]; [[arm]]}}. The ''-ko'' may be the same as in {{ja-r|海鼠|こ|pos=the historical name for "[[sea cucumber]]"}}, as both are soft-bodied marine organisms. Related terms could then be interpreted as {{ja-r|煎海鼠|いりこ|''ko'' eaten after being [[煎る|boil]]ed and dried}}, {{ja-r|海鼠|なまこ|''ko'' still [[生#Japanese|raw]]}}, {{ja-r|蛸|たこ|many-[[手#Japanese|armed]] ''ko''}}.<ref>{{R:ja:SMKGGJT|p=568}}</ref> Speculatively, the ''-ko'' element may instead be a diminutive suffix, commonly written as {{ja-r|子|-こ}}, related to {{ja-r|小|こ}}.

